Codex Usage Guide for GitHub-Connected Projects
1. Code Understanding & Documentation
- Explain any function, class, or module
- Generate docstrings or summarize large files
Example: 'Explain what workshop_service/main.py does.'
2. Generate or Modify Code
- Add new models, routes, or components
- Scaffold new microservices
- Improve or refactor existing code
Example: 'Add a Feedback microservice to store survey responses.'
3. Fix Bugs & Errors
- Identify and fix common coding errors
- Auto-debug based on error traces or test output
Example: 'Fix the bug in quiz scoring logic in main.py'
4. Add Features Across Services
- Implement full-stack features
- Add new database logic or endpoints
- Create frontend/backend integration flows
Example: 'Create a certificate download flow for completed students.'
5. Code Review & Suggestions
- Perform intelligent code review
- Suggest improvements to logic, style, performance
Example: 'Review frontend/App.jsx and suggest any code improvements.'
6. DevOps & Automation
- Create GitHub Actions workflows
- Write Dockerfiles and Compose files
- Setup CI/CD pipelines
Example: 'Add a GitHub Action to run backend tests on push.'
7. Code Navigation Help
- Search keywords across files
- Trace data flow and model usage
